Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper uses image processing techniques to improve the image of the self-portrait, which falls under the domain of computer vision.
- cs.GR (Graphics): The paper deals with the analysis and comparison of two portraits, which can be considered as a graphics-related task.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper may involve user studies or user interfaces for interacting with the processed images, which falls under the domain of human-computer interaction.
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with the processing and analysis of multimedia content (i.e., images), which falls under the domain of multimedia.
- cs.DL (Deep Learning): The paper may involve the use of deep learning techniques for image processing, which falls under the domain of deep learning.
